(6, 'Graduate Programs', '&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;\r\n	&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;images/master.jpg&quot; style=&quot;width: 600px; height: 200px; &quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;\r\n	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;\r\n	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;h3&gt;\r\n	&lt;strong&gt;Master of Thai Traditional Medicine Program&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\r\n&lt;div&gt;\r\n	&lt;strong&gt;Program Title&lt;/strong&gt;: Master of Thai Traditional Medicine&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;div&gt;\r\n	&lt;strong&gt;Full Title:&lt;/strong&gt; Master of Thai Traditional Medicine&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;div&gt;\r\n	&lt;strong&gt;Abbreviation:&lt;/strong&gt; M.TM. (Thai Traditional Medicine)&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;div&gt;\r\n	&lt;strong&gt;Study Time: &lt;/strong&gt;Two years with full time course&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;div&gt;\r\n	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;div&gt;\r\n	&lt;strong&gt;Objectives:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;ol&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n		To encourage the students to develop their knowledge of Thai Traditional Medicine theory and the ability to apply knowledge to other sciences.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n		To provide skills in Thai Traditional Medicine process research.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n		To engage in the development of Thai Traditional Medicine knowledge through processing of Sciences, Social Sciences and other relevant.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;\r\n		To utilize knowledge of the research to develop vocational study.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ol&gt;\r\n&lt;div&gt;\r\n	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;div&gt;\r\n	&lt;div&gt;\r\n		&lt;strong&gt;Curriculum:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n	&lt;div&gt;\r\n		&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;This degree is offered for undergraduate students with an emphasis on thesis research consisting of two plans in which the number of credits for each is at least 36 credit hours.&lt;/div&gt;\r\n	&lt;div&gt;\r\n		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n	&lt;div&gt;\r\n		Plan A (1)&lt;/div&gt;\r\n	&lt;div&gt;\r\n		&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;36 credits (thesis only)&lt;/div&gt;\r\n	&lt;div&gt;\r\n		Plan A (2)&lt;/div&gt;\r\n	&lt;div&gt;\r\n		&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; A minimum of required subject 12 credits and elective subject 6 credits and 18 credits of thesis are required.&lt;/div&gt;\r\n	&lt;div&gt;\r\n		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n	&lt;div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications of Applicants&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			Plan A (1) Thesis only&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;ol&gt;\r\n			&lt;li&gt;\r\n				Applicants must hold a Bachelor&amp;rsquo;s degree or expect to graduate with a Bachelor&amp;rsquo;s degree in Thai Traditional Medicine, Applied Thai Traditional Medicine or other related of Sciences.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n			&lt;li&gt;\r\n				Applicants must have a cumulative GPA no less than 3.25&lt;/li&gt;\r\n			&lt;li&gt;\r\n				For other related degree holders of Thai Traditional Medicine and Applied Thai Traditional Medicine, applicants must hold a license in any kind of Thai Traditional Medicine and through research or project of Thai Traditional Medicine; an approval from the Academic Committee is required.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n			&lt;li&gt;\r\n				Applicants who complete qualifications as above with a cumulative GPA no less that 2.75, having experience in Thai Traditional Medicine research and the research has been continuously published in national or international journal. This must be approved by the Academic Committee.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n			&lt;li&gt;\r\n				Other particular qualifications will be based on a specific announcement by the Graduate School, Prince of Songkla University.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n		&lt;/ol&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			Plan A (2) Thesis and Study&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;ol&gt;\r\n			&lt;li&gt;\r\n				Applicants must hold a Bachelor&amp;rsquo;s degree or expect to graduate with a Bachelor&amp;rsquo;s degree in Thai Traditional Medicine, Applied Thai Traditional Medicine or other related of Sciences and having a GPA of no less than 2.50&lt;/li&gt;\r\n			&lt;li&gt;\r\n				For other related degree holders of Thai Traditional Medicine and Applied Thai Traditional Medicine, applicants must hold a license in any kind of Thai Traditional Medicine.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n			&lt;li&gt;\r\n				Other particular qualifications will be based on a specific announcement by the Graduate School, Prince of Songkla University.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n		&lt;/ol&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			&lt;strong&gt;Admission Information:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Applications should submit the completed application form with all required documents in person at Graduate School, Prince of Songkla University&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			First Admission&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;ul&gt;\r\n			&lt;li&gt;\r\n				Apply online in October &amp;ndash; November&lt;/li&gt;\r\n			&lt;li&gt;\r\n				Apply in person in November&lt;/li&gt;\r\n		&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			Secondary Admission&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;ul&gt;\r\n			&lt;li&gt;\r\n				Apply online in March&lt;/li&gt;\r\n		&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			Selection Process&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;ul&gt;\r\n			&lt;li&gt;\r\n				Interview&lt;/li&gt;\r\n			&lt;li&gt;\r\n				PSU &amp;ndash; GET at minimum a score of 50%&lt;/li&gt;\r\n		&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			Expected Enrollment Number&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;ul&gt;\r\n			&lt;li&gt;\r\n				5 candidates accepted in academic year 2010-2013&lt;/li&gt;\r\n			&lt;li&gt;\r\n				10 candidates accepted in academic year 2014&lt;/li&gt;\r\n		&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			&lt;strong&gt;For Further Information:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			The Faculty of Traditional Thai Medicine&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			Tel:&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-tab-span&quot; style=&quot;white-space:pre&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &amp;nbsp; 0-7428-2708&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			E-mail: &amp;nbsp; mana.ra@psu.ac.th&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;santi.sa@psu.ac.th&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			Website: www.ttmed.psu.ac.th&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			Graduate School, PSU Tel: 0-7428-6981&lt;/div&gt;\r\n		&lt;div&gt;\r\n			&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n	&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;/div&gt;', 'nopic.png', '2010-06-23'),
(25, 'Visit to University of Health Sciences, Lao P.D.R', '&lt;p&gt;\r\n	&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Associate Professor Dr.Sanan &amp;nbsp;Subhadhirasakul, Dean of the Faculty of &amp;nbsp;Traditional Thai Medicine accompanied by Dr.Sasitorn &amp;nbsp;Chusri, Assistant Dean for Research and International Affairs, Dr.Nantiya Joycharat, Assistant Dean for Academic studies, and Miss Rattanavilai Thawornsuwon, International Affairs Officer, visited the faculty of Pharmacy, University of Health Sciences, Lao People Democratic Republic from 28 February &amp;ndash; 4 March 2011.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;\r\n	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;\r\n	&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;http://www.ttmed.psu.ac.th/english/images/lao1.jpg&quot; style=&quot;width: 300px; height: 225px; &quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;\r\n	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;\r\n	&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;The objective of the visit was to arrange the selection of students to be enrolled in the &amp;nbsp;bachelor and master&amp;rsquo;s degree courses at the Faculty of Traditional Thai Medicine. We also met the President of UHS and the president of the Faculty of Pharmacy to discuss the academic cooperation and announce our programs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;\r\n	&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;http://www.ttmed.psu.ac.th/english/images/lao2.jpg&quot; style=&quot;width: 600px; height: 172px; &quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;\r\n	We also had the chance to visit Viengchareun factory and Pharmaceutical Manufacturing Laboratory No.3 which produce traditional medicine.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 'news2-54.jpg', '2011-03-15');
